JsonSchema.Label: Platform Service Operator
JsonSchema.Hint:

JsonSchema.Label: Used for Azure DevOps?
JsonSchema.Hint:
An Azure DevOps tool is any service or tool used to support Azure production sites.

In all cases, these tools and services support internal consumption by developers, operators, support staff, etc. As we continue to extend the suite of DevOps tooling we use for internal consumption, some services and tooling may mature and become externally available as customer offerings (Azure Key Vault, Kusto, etc.). Functionally, we scope DevOps into the following core categories:

• Build – continuous integration tools, build status

• Live Site – troubleshooting, incident response/management, testing environment

• Package – artifact repository, application pre-deployment staging

• Release – change management, release approval workflow, release automation

• Deploy – production deployment tools and services

• Configure – infrastructure configuration and management, secrets management

• Monitor – performance monitoring, usage monitoring

• Capacity – capacity forecasting, planning, and management
JsonSchema.Name: AzureDevOpsTool
